  "title": "GRIT Trainee - [Business Development]",
  "description": "<p><strong>About Team</strong></p>\n<p>The Business Development and Partnerships teams at Shopee are dynamic and energetic. The teams are always looking to acquire business opportunities to drive Shopee to be the No. 1 e-commerce platform in Southeast Asia and Taiwan. The aim of the Business Development and Partnership teams is to provide Shopee’s buyers with a wide variety of product listings at the best prices.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>As a GRIT Trainee in the Business Development team, you will get the opportunity to gain real-world exposure, develop critical business skills, and contribute to impactful projects that shape the future of e-commerce.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<p>This is a 6 months full-time onsite role based in Singapore as part of the <a href=\"https://www.wsg.gov.sg/home/individuals/attachment-placement-programmes/graduate-industry-traineeships\"><u>GRIT Programme</u></a>. The GRaduate Industry Traineeships (GRIT) Programme is an initiative by Workforce Singapore (WSG)  that offers fresh graduates with traineeship opportunities across various sectors.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct competitor analysis and identify emerging market trends</li>\n  <li>Manage day-to-day coordination between sellers and internal stakeholders</li>\n  <li>Data analysis for brand performance review meetings</li>\n  <li>Conduct pitching of package to sellers</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Graduated or graduating in 2024 and 2025 from universities, or graduated earlier and completed National Service in 2024 or 2025</li>\n  <li>Singapore Citizen or Singapore Permanent Resident</li>\n  <li>Positive, team-player, and energetic attitude</li>\n  <li>Entrepreneurial spirit</li>\n  <li>Work well in a dynamic environment</li>\n  <li>Excellent in communication, enjoys interacting and forming relationships with partners</li>\n  <li>Analytical and comfortable with data, Microsoft Excel skills will be advantageous</li>\n</ul>",
